Gypsy is a one-year old female Lab mix, about 65 lbs. She is a super dog that is housetrained, leash-trained, knows sit, potty and goes to the door to be let outside. She might be best in an adult only home as too much activity seems to make her nervous.

ADOPTION FEES Dogs & Puppies.....$100.00 . This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more.
The first step to do an adoption is to do our Adoption Application here: https://www.elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
Yes, there are sometimes exceptions to our normal fee for older dogs or special cases. Some of our pets have also been lovingly sponsored by caring people and we will let the approved adopter know about that at the point of adoption. Visit our Website at: http://www.elmorehumane.org The staff would also like to remind you that for faster response to inquiries about adoptable animals to have the animals ID#, name & description. This way your questions will be answered in a timely manner.
All pet adoption websites & our shelter management software require that we choose a primary and/or secondary breed for our dogs. While our staff is quite breed knowledgeable, in many cases we are truly making our best guesses as to their breed(s) based on many factors but cannot promise that what we have said is accurate. So taking into account your own parameters for things such as size, coat care, activity level, etc please come and get to know our dog(s) as individuals to see if their personalities and yours are a forever match.
Phone: (334) 567-3377 Fax: (334) 567-8774 E-mail: hselco@bellsouth.net

Shy yet charming canine searching for a patient owner with a relaxed lifestyle. Looking for gentle guidance to help me come out of my shell. Treat me sweet and kind and I'll blossom. Recommend children 10 years and older.

This dog has special needs - they are heartworm positive. Dogs with heartworm disease can live happy, high quality lives as long as they are given appropriate care. We think that our heartworm dogs have just as much to offer their new adopters as any other dog and they deserve a chance at life! Heartworm disease is relatively common in the United States, so we are in need of caring adopters like YOU that are willing to open their home to a dog with heartworm disease. You are truly saving a life by adopting a heartworm positive dog!

All heartworm treatment expenses are the responsibility of the adopter.Due to COVID-19 protocols have changed.

Adoptions: If a person would like to adopt a pet, we encourage you to continue to monitor our website, which features our adoptable animals, and to also monitor our adoptable pet posts on our Facebook page. animal.description:
Reggie is an 8 year old black lab that spends most of his time laying at your feet. He is a sweet sweet boy that we have never heard bark, potentially because he can't, but also because he typically doesn't have a care in the world. We have had him for 3 months after he was found dehydrated, potentially having a heat stroke, and appeared to have been hit by a car. He doesn't move around too much but with a little encouraging he has started to go on walks and to dog parks this month (September). His pelvis was fractured before we got him but that has mostly resolved, although his legs give out from time to time. He also has laryngeal paralysis and pants pretty much 100% of the time. 

He would make a great companion for a less active family or individual that still moves around some but also like to spend days lounging at home. Please reach out if you think this might be your boy, he is seriously the easiest dog we have ever cared for and is enjoying his golden years happily.

To set up a meet and greet or inquire about a dog, please first fill out an application at https://savinghoperescue.org/contact. It doesn't obligate you, but it is the first step. We don't get to all of the inquiries but respond to all applications. Thank you for choosing to rescue!

animal.description:
Glam Maw

This sweet darling came to us a several weeks ago, after being found in the dumpster by a caring young lady. By the looks of her we thought she was an old senior dog... so we named her MeMaw.

We found she had a mammary tumor that had abscessed, along with many other issues. We also discover the cat loves her, and she loves cats too!

Surprisingly, Memaw is not 100 years old. She is only around 5 years old. This is what years of neglect did to this poor girl. Living in a crate and dumped like trash.

After arriving at Good Dog Headquarters, Misty said "girl, we can get you all fixed up!"

So we got on the phone with the plastic surgeon, raised a little money and got a mommy makeover. Only bad news was that during surgery the vet realized they needed to remove 3 of her breasts due to tumors. We are not going to stop until this girl gets the AMAZING home she so deserves! She is the sweetest girl and didn't know what love was till now.

A little nip and tuck does a body good.

Out with the old, in with the new! She went from MeMaw to "Glam Maw" and now she is bringing sexy back! She is so sweet and easy. Please think about opening your home up to Glam Maw. Thank you to all who helped with her care and continue to support her journey.
For more info call or text 903-235-0383, email agdadoptions@gmail.com or click the link below to fill out an adoption application!

http://plus.allforms.mailjol.net/u/b16bad72.php

Filling out your application is the first step of the process. Once we receive your application, it will be reviewed, then someone will get back to you within the next few days!

We will process all applications over the next few weeks before reaching out to potential adopters, please only send 1 e-mail with the answers below filled out.

Our Handsome Meatball is back, this poor guy cannot catch a break! Please, Please, understand he needs training, he needs exercise, he needs a home where he is the only dog and preferably older children (16+), he is the sweetest, goofiest dog, who just needs a human who will be patient and has time for training.

Meatball is a 4yr old, neutered male, Pitbull. I am going to tell you what we know about him and what he needs as this sweet baby needs the right forever home!!! What we know, he is eager to please, he loves to play, chase tennis balls, he is a goof, he has energy to burn, he loves to go on walks, he learns quickly. He loves loves loves food, very food motivated, this will help with training. He doesn't like big dogs or male dogs and no alpha dogs. He would make a great hiking, camping, walking buddy with training. He needs a fenced yard, no exceptions, he is not an apartment dog. 

My adoption fee is $200

1. Do you own or rent? 
2. If you rent can you get a letter form landlord stating you can have a Pit bull?
3. Do you have a nice size yard for him to run off energy? 
4. Do you have a securely fenced yard? 
5. How many people live in the home? Age groups? 
6. How many animals and types live in your home? 
7. Meatball needs training, do you have the time for this?

animal.description:
Chihuahua
Male, 12 years old, 7 pounds

Tiny Timothy isn't exactly like the character he is named after but there are some similarities! Tiny Tim does have some mobility issues that occasionally makes it hard to walk. He may have come from a "not-so-great" home before ending up at the shelter as he is terrified of many things. He is slowly but surely learning to trust new people. We hope this little guy will have a happy forever home for the holidays. 

Tiny Tim is looking for an adult-only home and one that has experience with anxious or frightened dogs is great. A patient, dog savvy person is what Tiny Tim needs to help him come around to understanding. He is not cuddly or affectionate at this time, but with familiarity and love shown him, he will grow to be a great addition to his future person's home. Tiny Tim is loving when he is not stressed but he is bitey when he is. He wags his tail in desire to be picked up. He becomes really happy when comfortable and gets along great with other dogs. He will ask his people to go up or down stairs and loves being able to get out in a yard. 

His mobility issues stem from significant arthritis and some disc narrowing along his lumbar spine -- it almost appears as if he may have had a previous spinal injury which has since healed. Both his patellas are medially luxated and will not return to their normal position, causing significant gait abnormalities and weakness in his back legs. There is also some mild arthritis in both knees as well. POMDR is consulting with an orthopedic specialist to find the best way to help his mobility. 

Tiny Tim joined us from the Santa Cruz County Animal Shelter after being found as a stray.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Golden Doodle - Requires an experience owner. Absolutely no young childrenTeddy is a cutie for sure. He is very strong willed and will require a firm, experienced hand. He spent 2 months with our certified trainer.
Older children only and no other dogs. Teddy is randomly selective.
Teddy was found running frantically around a Spring, Texas neighborhood. AARF Houston was called in to help. After scanning for a microchip, and none found, Teddy was placed in boarding while we searched for his owner. Teddy has been neutered, is up to date on all vaccinations and has been microchipped.
Teddy needs his own family to love him. Teddy needs a secure yard, and a family with older children (over 8) to help him become the boy he is supposed to be.
Is that famly you? =========================================================
Please contact app@aarfhouston.org for more information about this dog. You can apply online by clicking on Application .
Puppies that are under 4 months old cannot be adopted outside of our Veterinary Service area. Please call for specific locations. Children under 8 years old often are not a good match for our puppies and dogs. In order to protect both, your child and our rescued dogs/puppies from harm, we seldom if ever adopt to families with young children.
Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue! The adoption fee includes vaccinations, Bordetella, de-worming, rabies, spay/neuter and microchip. There is a an additional $12.99 fee for Home Again for a lifetime registration of the microchip.
Puppies cannot be adopted outside of the Houston area until they are spay/neutered after they are 4 months old. It is against the law in the State of Texas for a rescue not to be sterilized so we have to make sure it gets completed and that we have record of it.
NOTE: In our bios, we provide information based on our volunteer's experience with a particular dog; such as temperament, training, and ability to get along with others.
AARF is a 501(c)3 Non Profit, all breed, no kill organization. Our group is always in need of donations in order to continue to give the needed medical care to our rescues. Adoption fees do not begin to cover all of the medical costs. Any donation , no matter how small is a big help and is greatly appreciated. Please help us to continue to help them. Thank you.

animal.description:
MEET BOOKER

***POTENTIAL ADOPTER LOCATION REQUIREMENT- Our general adoption area is with a 50 mile radius of our Friendsville Home base - zip code  37737*** You can check to see if you fit within the radius at https://www.zipcodesoft.com/zip-codes-in-a-radius

Our adoption applications can be found online at www.tapsusa.org

I am an extra large 80ish lb big goofy and happy adult mutt.  I probably have some Lab, some Poodle, and some Irish Wolfhound in my DNA pool (I DO SHED - so if hypo allergenic is your vibe, I'm not a match).   l'd love a life where I get to take walks, get great care and lots of love in a stable low key household.   I may like to be the only spoiled child so I get all of the attention even though I like playing with other good natured dogs.  Did I mention that I would love a big tempurpedic dog bed?

Where can you meet me? (First fill out an application and then after it is reviewed and you are a potential match, you'll be contacted to set a meet and greet appointment time.)

OPERATION ADOPT
706 Kiser Station Road
Friendsville, TN  37737

BY APPOINTMENT ONLY

All animals are spayed/neutered, current on age appropriate vaccinations and microchipped before they go to new homes because that's the responsible way to keep them all safe.

To adopt one of our animals, the first step is filling out an adoption application at www.tapsusa.org Please make sure you get a confirmation that your application has been submitted. 

We only adopt to local homes  in the immediate vicinity because we utilize our volunteer force to process home visits.  Photos of your home, letters of reference are not acceptable which is why we only adopt locally. Only in very rare circumstances do we adopt out of area.  Examples of this would be finding the perfect home for a senior animal or one that has other special needs that we have not been able to place locally for an extended period of time.

He has a long fluffy coat that sheds like a northern breed, but a smaller face than the other dogs at the farm. If you are willing to forge a lifelong friendship, Rudy might be the guy for you! 
Rudy will need 6 foot fencing with dig guards, and to live in a legal area just to be safe.

animal.description:
Leonard

Arrives in Castle Rock tomorrow
Bassett Hound/Lab/Staffordshire Terrier fusion is out best guess 
1-3 years old
Dog friendly (would do best with another dog in the home)
No cats
Good with the kids he's met but he does get excited and jump 
House trained
Working on crate training and very eager to please so will be easily motivated 
Loves to play 
Heavy chewer
Loves to cuddle 
Very affectionate
Fully vetted beyond needing to be neutered
39lbs

Information from Leonard's Temp Foster

Leo is a true character....just watching him trot around the house with those short legs and turned out feet just makes me smile.

Leo was a bit skittish of me the first night, but he bonded immediately with the other dogs, especially my older German Shepherd. He was game to play with any of the dogs here, including my pittiie and a pit mix foster. He does not back away from a good wrestling match:)

Leo is NOT cat friendly.

He hasn't had any accidents in the house or crate ( including while I'm at work), other than marking his territory. I don't think he has ever met an object he didn't want to pee 
on:). He has a good appetite- I've been giving him 1.5 cups of dog chow, twice a day. 

He is not a huge fan of the crate, but has gotten a lot better about going in there, especially since I feed him in there. He may not want to go in the crate, but once in he doesn't whine or cry. 

Cold weather and snow don't seem to bug him.

Leo is an EXTREME power chewer- keep an eye on him! He seemed to like nylabones. 
He will also jump up on you- he might not be great with small children. 

While I think he would adjust fine to an only dog home, I think he would really thrive in a home with a slightly older dog who could mentor him. Once he saw my dogs interacting with me he warmed right up and now he loves me. He enjoys snuggling, licking arms and giving wet sloppy kisses. He always seems happy and ready to go with the flow. He was great with my two quirky females and he LOVES belly rubs. 

Leo is a pretty active dog. He's not super obedient, but he is smart and wants his people to love him, so I think he can be trained fairly easily.

We will miss this little guy, but he leaves us with lots of love and positive thoughts!

If you're interested in helping this amazing boy please contact us!

To Contact Us

Message us through our website http://www.highplainspaw.org

Message the Facebook Page at https://www.facebook.com/HighPlainsPAW

Fill out our Adoption Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/adoption-application

Fill out our Foster Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/foster-application

Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

Call our voicemail at (402)957-1578

 $200.00 Adoption Fee 
(Which is considered a non refundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we.) 

WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

 by Sybil

TALON HAS TO BE THE ONLY PET IN THE HOUSEHOLD. NO CATS OR OTHER DOGS.

animal.description:
Bubba is in a foster home, and is currently not at the shelter. Please find info below on how to adopt him, thanks.



Meet Bubba, a fan favorite amongst our dog behavior team volunteers! An easy-going boy at home, Bubba is an affectionate dog who enjoys leaning in for some good pets and prancing around with his toys. You can see him playing with one of his volunteer friends in his video below. 



On walks, Bubba feels conflicted about passing moving cars or people in close proximity and displays this with barking and pulling hard ("reactivity") so living in an apartment building or other densely populated areas can be very overwhelming for him. He would enjoy a home that has a fenced in area where he can feel comfortable outside and show off his great prance that he has! 



Bubba is looking for an adult only home that can continue the training he has been learning while here at Seattle Animal Shelter! Bubba would thrive with a family who is ready to give him the time and extra training to help him feel more comfortable while out on walks. 



Bubba likes to romp with toys and will always be happy to settle on a chew. He would like to be the center of your world and not share his home with other dogs or cats. He is very smart and active and will need a family where everyone is on the same page with his training and ready to establish a predictable routine full of physical and mental activities.



HOW TO ADOPT - Please fill out a Dog Adoption Application, available at http://www.seattle.gov/animalshelter/forms.htm and email it to the Seattle Animal Shelter Foster Dog Program at adoptionreview@gmail.com.



IMPORTANT NOTE: Many of our dogs will receive numerous applications, and the Seattle Animal Shelter asks for your patience during the process of finding the very best match. If you have questions about this dog that have not been answered above, please contact us at sasfosterdogs@gmail.com. If you would like to arrange to meet this dog, you must submit an adoption application. Thank you!

animal.description:
Instructions for finding your happy place: 1. Take time for yourself. 2. Get outside more often. 3. Fill out an application or me! My name is Zinn. I am a 2 year old, 30 lbs, male Blue Heeler mix. I am a social, confident, and loving guy!  Sometimes it takes me a few moments to feel comfortable in new environments, but with a confident leader at the end of my leash, I'll be relaxed in no time.  I am a sweet, sensitive boy who would love to have a happy, calm human bestie.  I am a sweetest boy this side of the Mississippi.  I am already a professional at both house and crate training. I am great with other dogs and would adore having some canine siblings. I am also friendly to cats and would do fine with older kids in the house. I’ll need a chain link fence in my forever home so no apartment or big rig life for me, please. I am currently in prison (known as Pups for Parole) and am learning so much cool stuff and all about how to be an amazing pup. I will be back shortly. For me, finding my happy place is easy, it is with you. So fill out that application for me, Zinn. 

I am currently enrolled in the Pups 4 Parole training program, learning all of the things I need to know to make me a great family member. I need someone willing to keep up my training so that I don't forget everything I am learning.

My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
This handsome man is Rocky! Rocky is a special fellow that needs a special home. Rocky was severely abused in his Puerto Rican home and when they got sick of him, they brought him to get euthanized. Thankfully the vet refused to do it and sent him to us instead. Rocky has some lasting effects from the abuse and he needs an owner that is understanding of that and will work through it with him. Rocky is a loyal companion. He will love his human unconditionally and protect them at all costs. He is super smart and extremely quick at learning new tricks. He is house and crate trained. He loves other dogs and even does fine with cats. 

Rocky's biggest issue is that he is scared to strangers (rightfully so), but it to the point that he feels he needs to be aggressive to protect himself from being hurt again. Rocky won't go looking for trouble, but if a stranger stands over him or puts their face in his face, he will stand up for himself. After knowing someone for a few hours, he is completely fine with them and will accept pets and love. He just needs to know that he can trust you first. Rocky does not like men and can not go to a home with a man or children. His abuser was a man, so of course he is extra scared around men. He doesn't dislike children, but children often don't understand that they can't put their face in his face, so we don't think it's safe to send him to a home with kids. When Rocky is comfortable with a person, they can do whatever they want to him and he won't care. We can run his belly, kiss his nose and pick him up. He just needs an owner that is willing to give him time to adjust. Once you give Rocky a chance, you won't regret it. He is so loving and playful. He will cuddle with you all day. He always looks at you with the biggest smile and follows you wherever you go! He is truly a wonderful dog. 

Please only apply for Rocky if you are understanding of his needs and are willing to continue with his training. You can apply for Rocky here: www.whenthegoinggetsruff.org/adopt

animal.description:
If you are looking for the nicest and happiest dog in Maryland then Bear is for you! He wakes each day with a positive attitude and has never met a human he does not like. That includes kids. He has plenty of energy and is up for any adventure you can think of. Bear loves walks, hikes, watching movies, exploring the yard, and taking naps. His absolute favorite activity, though, is Tug of War. He lives for this game and will take on anyone. Bear is completely house trained and is working on crate training. When left alone, he doesn't get into things or chew things that don't belong to him. He is a perfect gentleman! His foster family thinks he is perfectly behaved and he couldn't be any cuter! Bear is not really interested in other dogs. When sharing his home with another dog, he can become angry if the dog gets near his things or his people. Because of this, Bear must be the only dog. He is very interested in the cats, but because they run, no one is sure how introductions would go or if he would also guard his belongings. Bear's only Christmas wish is to have a home of his own to hang his stocking and wait for Santa to spoil him. 

Bear is currently undergoing Chemotherapy for Mast Cell Cancer.  He currently is cancer free but because his cancer was aggressive he is being treated in an aggressive manner in hopes that his cancer does not return.  Bear's medication is an oral pill and he will need monthly checkups with his oncologist until he completes his treatment.  Don't let Bear's cancer diagnosis deter you from adopting this guy.  Chemotherapy is very successful and Bear's cancer may never return. Pitties and Purrs is committed to completing his treatment so if you are interested in adopting Bear, we will continue to cover the cost of his appointments and medication.  We can discuss more specific details about his treatment once your application is approved.  

You must be over 21 and a home owner to adopt me. Please visit www.pittiesandpurrs.org to fill out an application. For further information contact adoptpitties@gmail.com

animal.description:
Meet Kirstyn, a three-year-old, 53-lb pittie gal who loves her people more than anything. Pets from her people. Kisses from her people. Literally just the mere presence (she'd prefer within 6 inches or less) of her people. But, because she loves her people so much, she tends to get anxious when they leave, can be unsure of how to respond sometimes, and always feels the need to protect - even when there's no need for protection. All that assumed responsibility and confusion she takes on can be stressful, which has at times led to aggression.

That's why she needs a family willing to work with her to show her what's okay to do, what's not, and that they're in charge and can handle things themselves. All she has to do is relax and be the cute, sweet pup she is. Kirstyn's current fosters have been working with a trainer to help show her that they're the ones who do the protecting. She's already catching on and doing very well. We're looking for experienced adopters who will be able to keep that kind of structure up and continue to advocate for her.

We'll require that Kirstyn's adopters continue to work with the trainer to keep her on the road to success and #nostress. She may take a little extra effort at first. But just look at that face and think of all the cuddles! This sweet girl is so, so worth it!

animal.description:
Betsy is a sweet, loving girl rescued from a high intake shelter in Memphis, TN. She is living in a foster home waiting for her forever family.

Betsy is one of the most happy, go lucky dogs in our home. She has played the companion dog to many of her foster brothers and sisters. She is our go to girl when introducing majority of the dogs, especially ones that are scared & uncertain. We believe Retriever can be found in Betsy's DNA because she loves water. She jumps in and out of the kiddie pool sometimes emerging her face in the water. She loves running and playing. 

Betsy is a special needs dog. Due to digestive problems, her preferred food is Pro Plan EN. We like to think of it as special food for a special girl.


If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.teammemphis.org under the Our Rescue page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers who work full-time jobs and have animals of our own, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.

animal.description:
Someone told Val that Santa is coming and he wants everyone to know he’s been a very good boy :) All Val wants this Christmas is a family of his own and he deserves it! Val is a young, handsome Pyr boy who was severely neglected before coming to NGPR. As a result of his previous situation, he suffered a break in his rear right foot that never healed properly. This hasn’t stopped Val from doing what he loves and being the sweetest boy ever. Val manages his pain by regulating his play and going to lay down when he gets sore. Meds will be needed for pain management as well. Val’s new family must be committed to monitoring this old injury and seeking appropriate care if needed. Val loves other dogs and will play for 10 minute intervals. He’s lived with cats, horses, and chickens and does well with all his animal friends. Val loves nothing more than to snuggle with his humans or curl up with a good bone. Val will quickly find a way into your heart with his beautiful loving eyes. He aims to please and listens extremely well. He is calm, gentle and promises to stay on the nice list! Apply for this sweet boy today and make his Christmas wish come true!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed. 

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

animal.description:
Argos is a 3 year old beagle that needs the following in a new home to succeed:

-No apartments- a country quiet setting would be best for him.

-A One Human Home-other pets are okay but we want a solo owner . Company is fine he is very social.  

-Beagle Experience

Argos is fully trained in off leash obedience by our good friends at Allied Dog Training.

He is a super social beagle- good with all animals and people.


Argos is a sensitive and emotional dog that thrives pleasing one human. Two humans can be hard for him as he loves rules and structure- he feels safe- two humans usually do not interact with a dog in the same manner.

He needs to have confidence and a single human home in the country would be ideal.

He needs a gentle leader to thrive and provide rules and structure .

He is great with all other animals. He even went to doggy daycare in the past.

He is a typical beagle and a leader or someone with breed experience should look no further!

Call or text Christine if you MEET the requirements 914-772-0649

Applications www.townandcountryk9resq.org under contact us.

Adopters will receive handling lessons from our trainers in Dutchess County NY

animal.description:
Baby is around 1 to 1.5 years old. She is believed to be a Husky Cattle Dog mix.    She is a beautiful dog that needs an active home and someone that will be her best friend.

She is very friendly to people. Very smart. She is an escape artist and if bored she will get out of a fenced yard. She can go over a six foot fence. The foster believes she would enjoy trick school.

Very loyal. She has spent a lot of time with Bret (foster) and she loves him. 

If she does get out all you have to do is drive to where she is even if it is next door and she is happy to jump in and go home. 

It took her a little more time to like being with the pack but she doesn’t mind now. She gets along with everyone but she would prefer to be the only dog or maybe just one other dog.

Cannot be left alone outside for one minute. She will either jump the fence or watch the gate for a chance. 

Needs to eat with no other dogs close. She was a stray and had to fend for herself so she should eat in her crate 


Baby needs someone that is very active. Take her to the park often and out in public. Really the person needs to be someone who their best friend is Baby and they do everything together. 

She is not a loud dog. Will bark some but basically pretty quiet. 

When left in the kennel it does need to be very secure. She gets in the kennel with no problem but if she sees a small chance to escape she will take it. I think maybe it just a challenge for her. 

Baby is spayed and up to date on vaccinations.

Meet Louie! This handsome young pit bull terrier mix boy is one year old. He is neutered, up to date on all his vaccines and heartworm/flea/tick prevention. Louie is a sweet boy and is good with older school aged kids (no young children because of his size) and other friendly dogs. He is a little too interested in cats so a home without them is recommended. He is not a high energy dog. He loves getting his exercise outside and relaxing on the couch. Louie is crate trained and is doing great with house-training with no accidents at his foster home. He will be a wonderful addition to your family with his very sweet and loving personality. Home ownership, a fenced yard and experience with the breed are requirements for adoption. Please make sure your local ordinance allows this breed. 
.WANT TO MEET THIS DOG?  CLICK ON  "More About Us' and choose APPLICATION LINK. 
Current on all vaccinations, heartworm negative on monthly preventative, microchipped 

Louie is in the Paws in Prison program where dogs receive obedience training. This dog is expected to graduate from Paws in Prison on1/5/21 . The dogs in this program are trained under the AKC Canine Good Citizen standards and are specifically selected to be family and companion dogs. They spend 24 hours a day with their trainers. For that reason, they will do best in homes where they are primarily inside dogs and spend lots of time with their families. The adoptive family will receive their training journal. This journal documents everything from entering the facility, daily training progress, and interactions with trainers.

Knows basic commands but will need training to come when called and leash walking. Duke does have diabetes and EPI (enzymatic pancreatic insufficiency). Diabetes is regulated with insulin shots twice daily and regulated meals and treats. EPI is regulated with a powder food additive twice daily (every meal). Adopters will need to be committed to the financial responsibility of regular veterinary visits, annual bloodwork and medication costs to keep his diabetes regulated. He does GREAT with his meals and medications. He gets VERY excited for food.

animal.description:
I'm Nome, or is that Noam, or maybe Gnome? (Any teachers doing a lesson on homophones? Here ya go!) Okay, it's NOAM. It used to be Gnome, when I was at Austin Pets Alive, and before that it was Max, and some of my friends still call me that.

That's one of the things about living a shelter/rescue life, you don't even get a name to call your own forever. And you sure don't get things of your very own, like toys and bones and treats that are still there when you come back if you didn't finish them right away. It's enough to make a guy kind of protective when he gets a hold of something good.

I am a wise, loving, kind old man, unless you try to take something away from me when I want to keep it. That's really pretty easy to manage, though. Just understand where that need is coming from, and you will want me to feel safe with my stuff.

I like meeting new people, and I could possibly live with another dog, and I am generally easygoing and cuddly and loving. I've had a very hard life. I still have a big scar on my leg from when I was shot, and for a long time I lived pretty much on my own, and then I lived in a kennel for a while. I've always had a few loyal friends, but I haven't been able to live with them. Now I live with this nice lady who understands me and wants me to have a comfy home where I will be safe and loved for the rest of my life.

I'm available for foster or adoption in the Austin, TX area.

animal.description:
Grizzle is a handsome man who's getting settled in at his foster home. We're learning a lot about him and it's all good stuff!

He's completely potty trained and has never had one accident! He follows his foster mom everywhere, like a shadow. He's also amazing on walks, he never ever pulls. 

Grizzle loves the dog park. He's quite popular with the other dogs and has human friends too! When he plays with other pups, he's really gentle. His signature move is to lick their face and give kisses constantly. He's absolutely amazing around new people and will cuddle/give kisses to any new person he meets.

Other favorite pastimes include: a good bone to chew on or a stuffed toy that he can rip the stuffing out of! Nothing gets him more excited than a Puppacino from Starbucks. 
He also loves a good afternoon nap and will let you know when he's recharged and really wants to play!


One thing we know for sure he doesn't like: his crate. He managed to escape it while leaving the doors still locked. So he's truly a Houdini. 

Grizzle is the perfect combo of energy and chill. He would be amazing in any home setting! Whether it's a quieter area or a loud one, nothing phases him. He would also be fine being the only dog but of course would love having another dog friend around. 

Est. Date of Birth: 12/23/2019

If it looks like love at first sight, head over to our website and complete an application! https://www.aliverescue.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Emmett was surrendered by a breeder to West Memphis Animal Shelter at 12 weeks of age. Emmett has a malformation of the spine, and his "look" didn't quite fit with this breeder's standards, so Emmett was passed off to the shelter. Fortunately, WMAS is a small shelter that treats their animals like family and seeks out the best for them. They contacted ALIVE Rescue, as they knew we've worked with special needs pups before. We took one look at Emmett and knew he needed to join the ALIVE Rescue family. 

Emmett was assessed at the University of Wisconsin, shortly after arriving with us. They felt Emmett's condition was congenital, and not related to trauma. They did not feel that an MRI would be appropriate at his age, and recommended if we were going to pursue that, to wait until he was done growing. They do not feel Emmett is in any pain. Emmett walks with ataxia and mild paresis of his hind limbs (left hind more then right hind), but guess what, NOTHING SLOWS EMMETT DOWN!

What we now know about Emmett is that he is a fully functional puppy, who has no idea that he has any limitations. Because he doesn't think he has limitations, we really don't either! He can go on walks and is excellent on a leash. He can urinate and defecate without assistance (but needs help with his schedule and potty training; he also wears a belly band because he has excited dribbles). He can chase a tennis ball. He can do exercises for his physical therapy. He can entertain himself hours upon hours with a stuffy. He can make friends with any human ages 1-100. He can make friends with any dog or cat that he meets. Emmett CAN DO anything he wants!

Now, what Emmett needs to do is find a foster or forever home to help him continue to shine. Emmett's ideal home will be a foster or a adopter that will do simple home exercises, daily, to continue to strengthen Emmett's hind limbs. Don't worry, we taught these to our volunteers and can teach them to you too! Emmett would enjoy joining a home with another pup, because he loves to play and have company (not a requirement but Emmett would count this as a bonus). 

Est. Birthdate: 01/03/2020

If Elvis were around today, he might look at Emmett and say, he "Ain't Nothin' but a Hound Dog," but he would be so very wrong. Emmett is so much more then just a hound dog, and he might just be one of the happiest pups we know! If you "Can't Stop Falling in Love" with Emmett, apply today to FOSTER or ADOPT him at http://www.aliverescue.org/adoption-application .

Meet Norman! 

Norman is a handsome, three year old Catahoula Leopard dog that is waiting to make a home with you.

Norman is a sweet boy who loves playing nicely with his doggie friends. Some of his favorite activities is rolling around in the grass and giving his humans hugs! 

While he enjoys life with his foster family, he can’t wait to find himself his own fur-ever home. He’s a bit shy when he first meets new people, but has been warming up to the idea of new people more and more! 

Norman is doing well with his obedience training, building up his confidence, and enjoys playtime. 

He is moderately active and would do well in a home that can give him a daily walk and play. He enjoys having a dog playmate but would also do well as the only pet. His ideal doggy playmate would be a female dog of any size or a male dog that is smaller than him. Norman is a bit overexcited around cats so would do best in a home without them. Young children are stressful for Norman so we will looking for a home for him without them. 

Checkout the video at the link below to see him socializing with other dogs.

Hi! Im Mr. Snuggles because I like to lay my head in her lap and snuggle under blankets. Ive only been living with my foster mom for just barely two weeks ,but she has already showed me what love is but, sometimes my foster kids calls me Aladin.

She found me roaming around a church parking lot near the woods. I was so itchy, starved,and tired. I was covered in fleas and ticks. She says she could barely see my fur. She took me to the vet to find out my collar was embedded into my neck and it had to be cut off. Im also heartworm positive. I actually just recently went back to the vet because i have a skin infection, and a terrible cough/gag. The vet said that its my heartworms and im breathing heavy. So im going to need an xray, and im starting the first round of heartworm treatment. My foster mom says its ok because there are people who care about me and theyre going to help me get better.

When I'm not spending my time at the vet or cuddling with my foster mom, I like to play with toys. I love toys! I also love getting my head rubbed and sitting for treats. I am really scared of the big black thing she calls the crate so i sleep on my bed next to her bed at night. I like to potty outside and do pretty well on a leash. Theres a lot of kids and kittens running around where im living and I just pay them no attention. Except the little girl, whos two, i like to bring her my toys to play. Shes never really interested though. I am so happy to see when my foster mom comes home I do the boxer wiggle and get very excited. I just can't help my self I've never felt this thing called love and it feels soo good! All I want is a chance at life to play and be loved!

Could you be my fur-ever home? If not can you donate to help me get better?

Love,

Mr. Snuggles

I am the perfect adventure partner and road trip companion, but I'm also someone you can sit and talk with since I'm a really good listener. I like to run with race team, and cuddle with my favorite volunteers, and I've got mad leash skills! I love playing with balls-tennis balls, soccer balls, basketballs, really any kind of ball will do-and I'm great at fetch! Did I mention, I also like car rides?! The volunteers call me "the whole package" and I'm game for showing you they're right. Come on by the SPCA or call and ask to meet me.

animal.description:
Jake
Breed: Lab mix
Gender: Male
DOB: 11/01/14
Adoption Fee: $175
Meet Jake...AKA: Jake from State Farm!!! Jake is a sweetheart that really wants to get out of the shelter and into a forever home!!! Jake is a special guy who needs to be the only pet in an all adult home. Jake is an easy-going boy that LOVES to go on long walks. Jake would benefit from some obedience training to help him become the best dog he can be!!! He would be a great companion for someone looking for a dog that isn't destructive and takes care of his toys & bed. Jake also seems to be completely housebroken. If you feel that your home is missing something, see if Jake is what you're missing!!!Please read the animal bios completely before requesting additional information as we do our best to answer the most frequently ask questions in these bios. 

In order to adopt one of our animals an application must be submitted and approved. You can find these applications by going to http://humanemorgan.org/index.php?page=adoption 

ABOUT ADOPTING FROM THE HSMC: 
The shelter address is 1170 Fairground Rd. Madison, GA 30650. For more information on any of our pets, please feel free to email us at INFO@HUMANEMORGAN.ORG give us a call at 706-343-9977. 
All dogs are heartworm negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
All cats are FeLv/FIV negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
We are open 10am-5pm Monday-Saturday, we schedule our last adoption at 4pm everyday to allow our staff enough time to feed and walk dogs. 
We are an animal shelter and therefore are not able to individually potty train our residents. Many adult dogs do arrive ""house broken"" however due to animal behavior any change in environment will make an emotional impact on the animals and therefore initiate unwanted behaviors during the acclamation period. Please keep this in mind. Puppies do not have the biological maturity to maintain absolute bladder or bowel control and will require a certain degree of potty training and house breaking. Please consider the time and commitment it takes to provide the necessary building blocks for these special babies, prior to submitting your application. 
If you have any questions please email us at info@humanemorgan.org and provide name of the animal you are interested in, in the subject line. 
Thank you, HSMC Staff 

ADOPTION FEES Adoption Fees may change without notice. Always verify the fee when finalizing the adoption. 
~ Cats and Kittens ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $100 
* 1-5 Years = $75 
* Over 5 Years = $50 
** Purebred cats and kittens may be subject to special pricing 

~ Mix Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $200 
* 1 -3 Years = $175 
* 4-8 Years = $150 
* Over 8 Years = $100

~ Purebred and Designer Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $375 
* 1-3 Years = $350 
* 4-8 Years = $275 
* Over 8 Years = $150 

~ Medical and Special Needs ~ 
We have rescued dogs and cats which require additional medical care or that have special needs which are not life threatening. In these cases we may require a higher fee to help recoup the costs of their care while at our rescue.

animal.description: Miss Ellie is a retired hunting hound that was surrendered to us a few months ago VERY pregnant. Ellie had one beautiful, healthy pup who has since been adopted. Ellie is a sweet old lady hound that enjoys the simple things in life - like long walks, snoozes in the sun, and cuddling on the couch. Ellie would prefer to be the only animal in the home soaking up attention and would not be a good candidate for living with smaller animals (as she has hunted previously). She could potentially live with another dog her size if they were on the more submissive side. She does live with three other dogs her size, but likes to control the fun level. She will let them know when the fun is over. Ellie loves people and is looking for some to call her own. She is around 8 years old, spayed, up-to-date on vaccines and heartworm negative. She is available for adoption with an approved application.

animal.description: Jenny is a loving and friendly girl, but was most likely found as a stray, and she takes a little bit of time to warm up. She wants to get to know you first before letting you take her out to dinner! Once she gets acquainted with her humans, her sweet personality comes out. She is still learning her house training and crate training skills, but she is eager to learn. She is great at home when people are around, but is still learning that her humans will come home. Jenny can be a little timid with being petted on the head. She is a fun, sweet, young girl that will need training. She can be strong on the leash, especially when other fun pup pals are around. She also loves plenty of bones and toys to keep her occupied! Jenny loves lots and lots of walks - the more the merrier! She is a great snuggling companion! She is a very loving and a happy dog that will make a great family member for someone who loves spending time and training their dog. She would also prefer to be the solo animal in the house because she's much happier when she can have all the attention. Come meet sweet Jenny, she's waiting for her furever home!

animal.description:
Ulysses, also known as Uli, is a sweet, shy gentleman who may need a little time to feel secure.  He is 8 years old and weighs 14lbs. Uli taught himself the doggy door.  He would do best in a single story home as he has not tried to use the stairs and does best when he can be around people.  He came to us with only 8 teeth, so his kibble needs to be moistened with a little water, other than that he has no special dietary needs or health issues. Uli gets along with other small dogs.  He does not like people messing with his face, but once he warms up, he will let you scratch his chin. Uli is not a fan of the crate so no crating for him. 

Please apply at tzuzoorescue.com if you are interested in adopting from Tzu Zoo Rescue.  More information available by contacting tzradopt@gmail.com.

[NOTE: We are a rescue NOT a shelter, meaning WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY THAT OPENS TO THE PUBLIC. Typically, an application and home visit (both of which are required for adoption) MUST be completed, BEFORE a potential adopter will be introduced to one of our pets, in order to first determine that our basic adoption requirements are met, prior to introductions being made. We also utilize personal reference and vet checks (to ensure that any pets already in the potential adoptive home are current on vaccines, heart worm prevention and sterilized) in our adoption process, all of which is intended to ensure that the best match, between pet and people, is made. The adoption fee is based on on the dog's age.

Hey there! My name is Deleon and I am a very sweet sweet boy! I am a senior boy, at 10 years old and 17lbs. and love to play with my collection of toys. I do good with most dogs but I do okay with myself too, as long as I have my toys. I also love finding my humans and sitting next to them to tell them I love them. I do have an enlarged heart but don’t let that stop you from giving me a home! I can still roam in the backyard and have some sunbathing time ( just no long walks). I love treats and will taste test them for you anytime- however my foster mom is making me go on a diet because she calls me chunky, so green beans it is. animal.description:
Born June 10, 2020, Sanka is a female purebred German Shorthair Pointer. Here is a little bit about her: Sanka is a goofy and loving pup who can’t seem to get enough snuggles. She was cleft but it does not impact her at all and her foster mom describes her as a happy and playful pup! She may have a slight vision impairment that makes meeting new people and dogs a little scary at first but she warms up in no time. Although she's a little hesitant with new dogs, once she knows them they are the best pals. She is almost completely house broken and has free access to the yard through a dog door. When she isn't playing, she can be found on the nearest lap for some snuggles. She loves to carry around toys and flip them in the air. Sanka's forever home will require a securely fenced yard and if there's children in the home, over 5 years old would be best. Applications can be accessed at www.mikeyschance.com

All large and/or active dogs will require a full fenced (6ft) secure yard. 
No children under 5. 

Like all Mikey's Chance dogs, this dog will come to you from a foster home that has provided loving one-on-one attention, socialization and some basic training, as well as quality food and exercise. 

Applications can be found at www.mikeyschance.com and completed on a computer, tablet, and/or phone. Please note that adopters are not chosen on a first come, first served basis, but full consideration is given to the best fit for the dog AND the adopter. Applications can take up to 3 weeks to process. Application submission DOES NOT guarantee approval for adoption.

animal.description:
This little dude is Macho! Macho is a very independent little guy who is a ton of fun when he gets to know you and feels more comfortable around you. He is super playful and loves long walks around the neighborhood, super social with everyone he meets! He doesn't like to be pet or held too much, but once he gets comfortable with you he loves to hang out and will give the most adorable little kisses and nibbles.
He needs an experienced and patient adopter who can work with him on learning to trust people and help him with some bad habits like resource guarding and some barking. He has anxiety and is on medication. He can bite sometimes when stressed. He is also scared of loud noises and will bark when he hears unexplained and very loud noises, like vacuums, blenders, and people walking in and out of an apartment. He would do best in a larger apartment or a house where he is not able to hear every noise! He is 4 years old and 11 pounds.

Do you have room in your heart and home for little Macho? Apply today!

animal.description:
Born May 6, 2008 Spunky is a male Collie mix seeking a forever home. This sweet senior is friendly, loving and gets along with other dogs. He wants a person or family of his very own to spend his "golden years". Spunky's ideal forever home is one with a secure 6 foot fence with adults or adults and children over 5. Applications can be accessed at www.mikeyschance.com

All large and/or active dogs will require a full fenced (6ft) secure yard. 
No children under 5. 

Like all Mikey's Chance dogs, this dog will come to you from a foster home that has provided loving one-on-one attention, socialization and some basic training, as well as quality food and exercise. 

Applications can be found at www.mikeyschance.com and completed on a computer, tablet, and/or phone. Please note that adopters are not chosen on a first come, first served basis, but full consideration is given to the best fit for the dog AND the adopter. Applications can take up to 3 weeks to process. Application submission DOES NOT guarantee approval for adoption.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Suzi!  I was found lost and alone wandering around a neighborhood.  A nice person out for an evening walk saw me and knew I needed help.  I am approximately two years old and I weigh 75 pounds.  My vet thinks I may be a Labrador Retriever Mix.  

I am a friendly girl and currently in a foster home.  I absolutely adore my humans.  I am working on my leash training and doing quite well with that.  I am house and crate trained.  I am a smart, friendly, beautiful girl.  My foster mom says I have kind, soulful eyes. I get along well with other dogs.  I have never been cat tested so my people are going to say no to a home with furry felines.  I would make the perfect hiking dog and would love to go adventuring.  If you want to relax, you should know I love to cuddle and have big dreams of being a lap dog.  I am a big girl so my people are going to insist on a home with a yard.  No apartments for this girl! 
    
I am spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccines.

animal.description:
READ THE FOLLOWING FOR INSTRUCTIONS ON SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION AND FOR A DESCRIPTION  OF THIS PET:

Beautiful Cas is a 2 year old boxer mix who weighs about 45-50lbs.  Cas needs to be rehomed as she and the alpha female in the home are not getting along, although Cas is just fine with the other resident dogs.  Her best friend is a male lab/dane mix and they play for hours without incident, so a home with an energetic male dog would be best for Cas.

Cas is great with all people, although she is pretty energetic and would do best with older kids.  Cas loves to be outdoors, so a fenced in yard or a runner/hiker/active person and are must haves for this girl to be happy.  

No kittens or other small critters for Cas please, she has a strong prey drive and although she has never hurt a small animal, she is way too interested in them.  Dog savvy older cats have not been a problem for Cas, she just likes to chase the younger ones too much.

Cas' adoption fee is $350.  She is fully vetted and ready for her new home, please consider this sweet beauty!

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING, PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING INSTRUCTIONS:

- The first step towards adoption is to complete an adoption application, which can be found online at our website www.roadtriprescues.com, under the “ADOPT” tab.

- Do not use the Petfinder links or email to ask us about our adoptable dog listings - we do not always receive these messages and will not respond to them.

- Please do not ask if a dog is still available - we do our best to update their status as quickly as possible.  If a dog is listed for adoption, it means we have not yet approved an adopter and are still accepting applications.

- PLEASE NOTE THAT ONLY APPROVED ADOPTERS WILL BE PERMITTED TO MEET OUR RESCUES - WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE AND ALL OF OUR DOGS LIVE WITH US AS FAMILY. 

Thanks for considering a rescue pup!

Please read this section to the end. Be 100 Percent certain you are ready to adopt.
If you are seeing the dogs listing, the dog is adoptable- the site is updated several times a day. 
Include all information the application is requesting, or your application will not be considered. 

ALL OF OUR PUPPIES DO NOT LEAVE UNTIL THEY ARE 12 WEEKS. PUPPIES WILL NOT LEAVE WITHOUT ALL VACCINES AND SPAY AND NEUTER SURGERY COMPLETED- NO EXCEPTIONS
Please do not text or call the number listed on the site, email only. 
If you have a question that is not addressed in the information section, you are currently reading you may email us. 

Hi, my name is Chewie. I’m a 5-7 year old chihuahua. I was a feral(wild) chi before being rescued by Canine Pawsabilities.
I came to stay at Chimama’s Bed and Breakfast in August where the beds are soft and breakfast is delicious.
Chimama says I’ve come a long way but still have not completed my journey. I still have trust issues that will need work with. I need someone to be kind,loving, understanding and patient. I will come when called, give kisses, cuddle with you on the couch and be your loyal friend when we build a trusting bond.
I’m only in a crate for night time and when Chimama runs errands. I over heard her say she was going to try to take me to bed to see if I would be compatible bed mate. I potty outside but I have been known to sneak a pee or poop in the house. It happens sometimes. So I need a home with a fenced in yard to do my business. I am not leash trained. So I’ll need lot of help with that. I will occasionally play with a toy but I’d rather sit with you.
So if you have love, patience and time I have the licky kisses.Dog and cat friendly children over 12 

Adoption fee of $250 includes:
-yearly dhpp vaccine 
-bortadella vaccine 
-rabies vaccine 
-spayed
-heartworm negative status
-wormed several times and fecal tested negative
-heartworm prevention up to date
-flea and tick prevention up to date
-microchipped
-dental 
-health exam completed 

Applications accepted at the following link: 
https://form.jotform.com/201418465695159

animal.description:
****Please do not send us inquiries/emails asking if this dog is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. See the bottom of this bio for more FAQs regarding our adoption process before emailing.****

Name: Olive

Age: 3 years

Current Weight: 40 pounds

Rescued from:  Texas

Olive was rescued from an area where there is an abundance of homeless dogs, and not a lot of shelter space for them to go while they wait for their forever homes. She will be arriving at SNARR's Adoption Center in Brewster, NY on December 30th  ready for adoption!

Health: up to date on required vaccines

Hi, my name is Olive. I didn’t have a good life living on the streets of Houston until I was rescued. I had to have surgery so I’m a tripod and have one eye. I am very friendly but some mean human shot me and that caused me to have permanent incontinence. But that doesn’t stop me. I adore being outdoors. I really enjoy people watching when my humans let me out in the gated front yard. I love to play fetch, tough of war and hide and seek with my human foster sisters and I absolutely love toys. They say I have a great personality. I have to wear diapers and my foster mommy got me some cute ones in different bright colors. I love other dogs and humans of all sizes, and I am especially amazing with the smaller ones. I am crate trained, ride well in the car and I take treats gently. I am spayed, heartworm positive and going through slow kill heartworm treatment. I would prefer a home with little humans and at least another dog to play with me but I wouldn’t mind being an only dog to get all the attention. If you are looking for a petite girl with lots of love to give, I am your match.

Adoption fee: $300

IMPORTANT: This dog has not yet been altered. For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

To apply to adopt Olive, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 
**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING

**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary
